commit_list.message: Refactored out a needless triggerEvent implementation.

Trigger JavaScript events on any object.

For example, you could now emit events on window instead of document.
Support JavaScript confirm() dialog.

Hide macgap.notice interface when OS X doesn't support it.

This allows the app to use Notification Center when it's available, but
fall back to Growl messages. The app could also choose to always use the Growl
interface.

Save window size and position.

Window size can be set using macgap.window.resize(), but if it's not,
last known window size and position is used. This gives more control to the
end-user.

Use File.read instead of `more` in extconf.rb.

In some contexts, `more` will require user input before returning, hence
blocking deployments or CI runs.

Reconnect after receiving callback.

When an EventSource server is restarted, em-http-request might
send the callback event instead of errback. We also want to
reconnect in that case.
